&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maintenance Carpenter Builder&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at Hillingdon Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be carrying out minor repairs and routine planned maintenance on our building fabric ensuring compliance with Trust safety standards and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To carry out new and maintenance carpentry work on building fabric within the Trust’s areas of responsibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of high quality health services to the local population by the provision of a comprehensive, responsive estate maintenance service, resulting in a high quality safe environment for patients, staff and visitors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have relevant experience having demonstrated high versatility and flexibility. You will be expected to attend further training courses as necessary. It may be necessary to work at weekends and outside normal working hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full current UK driving licence would be beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion on this post, please contact Anish Haria Building Estates Officer on 01895 279720&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
